    "client_msg_id": "8216436d-4ab9-421f-8c9c-7626857a67ad",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "Did you ever look into Fiat? I saw it come up in the comments and after skimming the paper, my interest is piqued!\n\n&gt; The foundation of deductive synthesis in Fiat is _refinement_: a user starts out with a high-level specification that can be implemented in any number of different ways and iteratively refines the possible implementations until producing an executable (and hopefully efficient) implementation.\n<http://plv.csail.mit.edu/fiat/papers/fiat-popl2015.pdf>\n\nHowever, I have no experience with this notation, so I can’t understand almost any of the figures…",
